Comment:
Wow I am... very concerned about this movie now, very concerned. Deadpool isnt a very complicated character to represent, hell he has dozens of video game and animated variations that all, for the most part, succeed, giving us a fun, colorful Deadpool persona... this right here... is not Deadpool. Im baffled that through all Ryan Renolds talk of being such a super fan to Deadpool, he acts nothing like him, at least from the whiffed humor here in this trailer. 

When youtube channels can bring out Deadpool's persona better then you can in a trailer... that should be your first sign that somethings gone terribly wrong.

Comment: Lots of people asking about 4th wall breaking and how heavily it will feature. I'm sure most of us here have read the comics and know that deadpool breaking the forth wall happens most often when it's just deadpool and the audience alone. He talks to us when no one is around. There will be lines here and there that will be directed towards the camera, and there will be references to real world things like the green animated suit. This is a forth wall break because its not acknowledged by the people in the movie. The forth wall is practically a deadpool trademark. He'll be breaking that more than he's breaking bones. Trust me.

Title: Deadpool | Red Band Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment:
The only issues I have from seeing this trailer is:

1. A lot of the action scenes in the trailer seems to be on that highway overpass. I'm hoping that his origin story doesn't take an hour so we get action the last 30 minutes or so. And also more variety to where he goes. If we do get a long origin story, I trust that Deadpool's character will make it a fun ride though.

2. I felt like the test footage nailed the "red suit, brown pants" joke. Maybe having a pedestrian passing by, staring at Deadpool until he starts, "You must be wondering why the red suit, blah blah blah" Then when he notices the trucks, he turns to the camera (or back to the pedestrian) and finishes the "brown pants" portion. Seems like it was kinda forced in here for the sake of having it in there because it was also in the test footage. 

Everything else seems pretty true to the character.

The Charleston shooting is yet another massacre orchestrated by people with advanced technology. The victims under the control of this
technology, such as Dylann Roof, are known as or "zips" or "zipper guns". If you have watched The Sopranos (the characters are based on people
from my local area), you may have heard them use the term "zip". This word is used to describe assassins from Italy who are used to do the dirty
work for Tony Soprano and his crew, and their presence in the show is a metaphor for people under the control of this technology. There are a few
scenes in The Sopranos where Tony plays golf, which is a metaphor for radome sites such as the CIA-ran Menwith Hill in the UK. These facilities
give use of their technology to The Freemasons. There is another mention in the media of this technology in an interview between Bill O'Reilly
and Jon Stewart. Jon Stewart says, "Oh come on Bill, we're both members of the media elite here", to which Bill O'Reilly replies, "Oh yeah? How

Title: Deadpool | Red Band Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment:
Love Deadpool as he's my favorite comic book character of all time--the only one I ever liked enough to actually buy a comic (outside of like, Archie), mostly because of the humor. It's something I can really relate to--the sort of inside jokes for the culturally literate. Heck, I actually research the stuff he references sometimes.

Hopefully though, the jokes are better than (most) of these. Sorry, call me a conservative but I know Deadpool can be funny without the cursing or the R-rated humor and obscenities. Though I can appreciate the need for the R rating, I found Deadpool funniest breaking the 4th wall and making references in the comics or just being in absurd stories. Love the Green Lantern joke and it took awhile to get the brown pants joke. So, here's hoping for more intelligent humor jokes that transcends the crude.

Kinda relitiveDeadpool: Red band Speculation
I have a feeling the deadpool movie not going to be too good but everyone is going to back it up because its deadpool, don't get me wrong deadpool is my favorite superhero and I love the comics and the game esspecialy the humor, but the trailer for it kinda put me off.

The humor was... different to the comics, it was more "random" and seemed more forced, and unnessisary. And when he goes "I'm going to touch myself tonight" after fighting tons of what we know are bad guys and inhaling somke from his guns made me kinda upset.
This goes for the wrighting, its just dosent feel right. The CGI and cinematoegraphy looks good, yet we don't know much about the actual story other than how its a origin story (I hope it dosent drone on). It dosent even show us why he fights crime.
(I mean most of us already know why but its kinda crutial to put in a trailer.)

Well its just a trailer and I'm going to watch it anyway, maybe it will be great.
But we just have to wait and see.

Don't agree with me, then explain your opinions and why you disagree.
Thanks for reading.

Comment: To those arguing about whether or not the Green Lantern reference is "breaking the fourth wall," it is. Breaking the fourth wall means the character does something that indicates that this character isn't real, or that they know they are in a movie (or tv show, or play, etc.). By alluding to GL, this also alludes to Ryan Reynolds existing, which means this character is not a real person. And to those calling it an "Easter Egg" I say this: you have to hunt for Easter eggs, just like the real things. They are not shouted at you, nor are eggs hurled at you on Easter.

Is it just me or do Ryan Reynolds and Nathan Fillion's careers keep intersecting in one way shape or form. They worked together in "Two Guys and a Girl" (and a Pizza place). Then Fillion was rumored to be one of the final choices for the live action version of Green Lantern (dogged a bullet on that one) which ultimately went to Reynolds (hence the superhero suit not green or animated joke from this trailer). Then Fillion became the voice actor for Green Lantern in some animated movies. And now Ryan is acting opposite Morena Baccarin in this movie and she also starred in "Firefly/Serenity" with Nathan Fillion.

Good trailer by the way.

Comment:
After the disappointment that was Green Lantern according to some people,i didn't see Ryan Reynolds playing another super hero or anti-hero ever again in his career.But than again,if Ben Affleck can put on the Bat suit after many criticized him for his portrayal of Dare Devil,one can only hope this movie will be good,if not great.

This role seems more fitted to Ryan Reynolds acting and/or comedic skills than such a serious character like Green Lantern.He was not the right guy for that role.So far this trailer shows promise with its material and mature approach.Hopefully it wont be marginalized the same way Watchmen was for its content.Some people have a distorted view of superheroes/comic books expecting it to be squeaky clean like Spider-Man,Superman or some brady bunch episode.

Title: Deadpool | Red Band Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment:
I kinda wish the tone didn't waver so much. For a comic book, that tonal impermanence, always shifting and changing, can be effective story-telling. But in a movie, especially one trying to capture the attention of a couple of different age demographics, despite the liberal use of a hard R rating, that can muddle up the final product.

I wasn't expecting it to be straightforward-linear-movie-film-for-theaters out the gate. An actually origin story. I hope those flashback moments are given more levity and irreverence. You can't generate sympathy for such a crass, vulgar, 4th-wall breaking, meta character by showing how he USED to be. There are more clever ways to inform Wade Wilson's character through his actions.

Bah, now I'm rambling. I'm hyped for this flick. Just... cautiously hyped.

Comment:
Перевод на русский:

- Я люблю тебя, Уэйд Уилсон. Мы сможем побороть это вместе.
- Ты права! Рак распространился только по моей печени, легким, простате и мозгу. Органам, без которых я легко обойдусь.

-
Что, если бы я сказал вам, что мы можем сделать вас лучше? Вы - боец. Мы 
можем дать вам способности, о которых большинство людей лишь мечтает. Мы
можем сделать вас супергероем.
- Просто пообещайте, что не обманите меня. Чтобы я не обманул кое-кого ещё.

- И пожалуйста, не делайте мой суперкостюм зеленым! Или мультяшным!

- Ни один человек, что вышел отсюда, не сохранил своего чувства юмора.
- Посмотрим, леденец! Эй, ну чего ты? Ты оставишь меня здесь с менее гневной версией Рози О'Доннелл?

- Погодите!!! Возможно, вы задаетесь вопросом, почему у меня красный 
костюм. Ну, это чтобы плохие парни не видели, как у меня течет кровь. 
Этот парень уловил мою идею! Он надел коричневые штаны!

- Папочке пора выплеснуть немножко ярости.

- Вот же выблядок! 

- Здесь пахнет штанами старой бабули.
- А ты звучишь, как будто у тебя хуй во рту.

- Оу. Блядь! На тебя тяжело смотреть.
- Как яйца с зубами.
- Ты выглядишь, как если бы Фредди Крюгер вы*бал в рот топографическую карту Юты.
- Именно!

- Сегодня вечером я трахну сам себя.

- Какой же ты чудовищный. Ты выглядишь, как будто авокадо занялся сексом с еще более несвежим авокадо.
- Спасибо!

Comment:
That quote about Deadpool wearing red and the guy wearing brown pants reminds me of a joke from Bill Engvall.

There's this pirate captain sailing upon his ship out at sea with his crew; man in the crow's nest calls out an enemy ship on the horizon, and the captain says "Bring me, my red, shirt." He gets it on and they succeed without any losses.
Next day a crew member asks why the red shirt, captain says, "It's so that, in case I get shot and bleed, the crew won't notice and they'll continue fighting".
The guy in the crow's nest calls out 20 enemy ships on the horizon and the captain replies with, "Bring me my Brown Pants!" XD


Part of me feels like someone in production either heard that joke, or watched Bill Engvall or Blue Collar Comedy

Title: Deadpool | Red Band Trailer [HD] | 20th Century FOX
Comment: People need to know that Deadpool ISN'T a Superhero. He's a mercenary with super-human regenerative powers and multiple personality disorders who mostly does everything for money. Yeah, there will be grandstanding with cheesy/lame 1-liners because the guy is crazy, says whatever comes to his fractured mind. No one in the comic can stand him because he NEVER shuts up and enjoys doing the killing -- most of the time. If you understand this, you will like the movie. If you go in thinking he's supposed to be like one of the Avengers or an X-men, you will be sorely disappointed.
